<a href="/blog/2012/12/03/spring-integration-2-2-0-ga-has-been-released"><h2 class="member-post--title">Spring Integration 2.2.0 GA has been released</h2></a>
<div class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2012-12-03 16:55:00.0">December 3, 2012</time>
</div>
</div>
</header>
<section class="member-post--summary"><p>We are pleased to announce that <a href="http://www.springsource.org/spring-integration" target="_blank">Spring Integration</a> 2.2 is now GA.</p>
<p>The artifacts are available in the <a href="http://repo.springsource.org" target="_blank">SpringSource Repository</a> as well as Maven Central, or you can download the zip <a href="http://www.springsource.org/download/community?project=Spring%20Integration" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>
<p>For a big picture view, please read the <a href="http://static.springsource.org/spring-integration/docs/2.2.0.RELEASE/reference/htmlsingle/#whats-new" target="_blank">“what’s new”</a> section of the reference manual.</p>
<p>For more detail on some of the main additions, refer to the following blog series:</p>
<p>Part 1: <a href="http://blog.springsource.org/2012/09/24/whats-new-in-spring-integration-2-2-rc1-part-1-mongodb/" target="_blank">MongoDB Adapters</a><br>Part 2: <a href="http://blog.springsource.org/2012/09/26/whats-new-in-spring-integration-2-2-part-2-transaction-synchronization/" target="_blank">Transaction Synchronization</a><br>Part 3: <a href="http://blog.springsource.org/2012/10/05/whats-new-in-spring-integration-2-2-part-3-jpa-support/" target="_blank">JPA Support</a><br>Part 4: <a href="https://spring.io/blog/2012/10/09/what-s-new-in-spring-integration-2-2-part-4-retry-and-more" target="_blank">Retry and More</a></p>
</section>
